                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" hclass="sense" id="edwardalbee_sng_1" htag="li"><span class="sensetop" hclass="sensetop" htag="span"><span class="def" hclass="def" htag="span">(1928-2016) a US writer of plays who became famous for <span class="ebi">Who's Afraid of Virginia Woolf?</span>(1962). He later won the <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/pulitzer-prize" title="Pulitzer Prize definition"><span class="ndv">Pulitzer Prize</span></a> three times, for <span class="ebi">A Delicate Balance</span> (1966), <span class="ebi">Seascape</span> (1975) and <span class="ebi">Three Tall Women</span> (1994).</span></span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
